"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-2024-paris-olympics-surfing-round-1\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Fans around the world are eagerly awaiting the opening rounds of the2024 Paris Olympic Gamessurfing competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 112, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fans\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 4}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 12, \"to\": 21}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening rounds\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"the2024\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 72}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris Olympic Gamessurfing competition\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 111}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, unlike the other events in the Summer Olympic Games, the date is not written in stone.\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other events\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 173}, {\"ngram\": \"the date\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 183}, {\"ngram\": \"stone\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sohow does the surfing competition work?\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 249, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the surfing competition\", \"from\": 220, \"to\": 243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearly 10,000 miles away from the home site of the Paris Games, the surfing athletes are preparing to ride a monster wave in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9393123425910603e-14, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the home site\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 312}, {\"ngram\": \"the surfing athletes\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"a monster wave\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The exact launch of their competition will depend on weather and ocean conditions.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The exact launch\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 399}, {\"ngram\": \"their competition\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"weather\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"ocean conditions\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The very first day for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe Call\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d will be July 27.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The very first day\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe Call\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 503}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that day\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s forecast looks promising the competition will be given the go-ahead.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that day\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s forecast\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"the go-ahead\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Round one will see all surfers on both the men's and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sides take the water.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Round one\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"all surfers\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"both the men\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 669}, {\"ngram\": \"sides\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be in heats of three with the winner moving straight to the third round.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heats\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 713}, {\"ngram\": \"the winner\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"the third round\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 773}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two other athletes from each heat will have to battle it out once again in the second round based on scores, with the loser of that heat going home.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The two other athletes\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"each heat\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"the second round\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"scores\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"the loser\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 902}, {\"ngram\": \"that heat\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men:Heat 1- Ethan Ewing (AUS), Tim Elter (GER), and Jordy Smith (RSA)Heat 2- Joan Duru (FRA), Jack Robinson (AUS), and Matthew McGillivray (RSA)Heat 3- Alonso Correa (PER), Filipe Toledo (BRA), and Kanoa Igarashi (JPN)Heat 4- Gabriel Medina (BRA), Connor O'Leary (JPN), and Bryan Perez (ESA)Heat 5- Ramzi Boukhiam (MAR), Billy Stairmand (NZL), and Jo\\u00c3\\u00a3o Chianca (BRA)Heat 6- Andy Criere (ESP), John John Florence (USA), and Alan Cleland (MEX)Heat 7- Kauli Vaast (FRA), Lucca Mesinas (PER), and Griffin Colapinto (USA)Heat 8- Rio Waida (INA), Leonardo Fioravanti (ITA), and Inaba Reo (JPN) Women:Heat 1 Yolanda Hopkins (POR), Caroline Marks (USA), and Sarah Baum (RSA)Heat 2 Sol Aguirre (PER), Janire Etxabarri (ESP), and Vahine Fierro (FRA)Heat 3 Anat Lelior (ISR), Sanoa Dempfle-Olin (AUS), and Tyler Wright (AUS)Heat 4 Tatiana Weston-Webb (BRA), Molly Picklum (AUS), and Caitlin Simmers (USA)Heat 5 Johanne Defay (FRA), Brisa Hennessy (CRC), and Candelaria Resano (NCA)Heat 6 Tain\\u00c3\\u00a1 Hinckel (BRA), Camilla Kemp (GER), and Luana Silva (BRA)Heat 7 Nadia Erostarbe (ESP), Siqi Yang (CHN), and Saffi Vette (NZL)Heat 8 Carissa Moore (USA), Teresa Bonvalot (POR), and Matsuda Shino (JPN) There are some past Olympic and World champions in the mix this year in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": [{\"be